<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Notes===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* To add objects to a {{Incode|LinkGroup}} after its creation, drag and drop objects into the group in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]].
* In groups where {{PropertyData|LinkMode}} is set to {{Value|Auto Delete}}, removing an object from the group or dragging it out of the folder will permanently delete that object from the document.
* When {{PropertyData|LinkTransform}} is {{Value|True}}, the link's {{PropertyData|Placement}} becomes a read-only indicator (shown in green). To move the link, you must modify the (usually hidden) {{PropertyData|Link Placement}} property.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Properties==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Data ===
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{TitleProperty|Link}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Placement|Placement}}: Standard placement of the LinkGroup. Objects inside the group are positioned relative to this coordinate system. In other words, moving a LinkGroup moves all its contents in the 3D View.
* {{PropertyData|Link Mode|Enumeration}}: Controls the automated behavior of the group when objects are added or removed:
** {{value|None}}: The group acts as a simple container. Removing an object from the group does not affect the object's existence in the document.
** {{value|Auto Delete}}: The group assumes ownership of its contents. If an object is removed from the {{PropertyData|Element List}} or dragged out of the group in the Tree View, the object is permanently deleted from the document.
** {{value|Auto Link}}: If a document object is added to the group, the group automatically wraps it in an [[App_Link|App Link]].
** {{value|Auto UnLink}}: A selective cleanup mode. It distinguishes between objects that the group created automatically (such as "helper links" generated via the {{value|Auto Link}} mode) and objects that the user manually moved into the group. It will only delete the objects it created itself; any "guest" objects the user added are preserved when they are removed from the group.
* {{PropertyData|Element List|LinkList|Hidden}}: An internal list of references to the document objects contained within the group.
* {{PropertyData|Visibility List|BoolList|Hidden}}: A boolean list that stores the visibility state of each item in the {{PropertyData|Element List}}. This allows the group to manage the visibility of its contents independently of the objects' own settings. To edit or view this property in the Property
</div> 

